Path: This week in Nu #50
Content:
JosephTLyons fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2271] histogram example
, renamed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2283] -f to -l in 
``ls``
 and 
``ps``
, did some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2290] internals cleanup
jonathandturner removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2282] build.rs pre-build steps
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2291] --partial to 
``to html``
, added support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2309] ``do -i``
 to also redirect stderr
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/demo/pull/55] more columns to 
``ls``
 in demo
thegedge updated the first parsing stage to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2284] return partial results
jzaefferer updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2285] docs for alias
, added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/demo/pull/48] ribbon and WIP note to demo
, optionally 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/demo/pull/49] pivot table on overflow in demo
, added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/demo/pull/50] loading indicator for the demo
, switched demo to using 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/demo/pull/54] ``to html --partial``
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/57] link to demo and fixed link to blog on main site
, copied 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/56] CONTRIBUTING info to main site
coolshaurya updated 
``str collect``
 to take 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2289] an optional separator
bailey-layzer added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2292] the 
``reduce``
 command
kornelski moved Nu to use 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2293] the supported app-dirs crate
k-brk added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2298] ``str contains``
 and 
``str index-of``
andrasio did an 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2299] overhaul of how data reporting works internally
, added support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2300] regular values in 
``histograms``
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2310] samping support for variance and standard deviation
nmandery added support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2303] parsing many more date formats
fdncred updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2305] rustyline default configuration
candostdagdeviren added links for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-book/pull/27] ``Tagged<Value>``
 and 
``ShellError``
 in the docs
homburg added comparison of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/118] Nushell and Bash output to the book
RFCs:
jonathandturner proposed a new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/rfcs/pull/3] data representationt to replace the current Row/Table model
